    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "b4c8cc57_7caad320",
        "filename": "logdog/api/endpoints/coordinator/services/v1/service.proto",
        "patchSetId": 3
      },
      "lineNbr": 157,
      "author": {
        "id": 1109829
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-10-06T00:43:52Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I like \"oneof\" for a few reasons:\n- It avoids the need to build multiple independent for loops.\n- It reduces the number of position relationships between this and the response to a single slice.\n- It represents the intent to the user, which is that there is a list of requests and a set of responses.\n\nA \"repeated\" element would require a repeated response and multiple associations. It would also require independent iteration for each repeated element. Finally, if a new element is ever added, right now we\u0027d get an error b/c of no type match in switch, but in a \"repeated\" case nothing would exist to notice that there is a field being ignored.\n\nIf there isn\u0027t a major objection, I\u0027d like to keep this as-is in this respect.",
      "parentUuid": "a38c57e1_a943ee0d",
      "revId": "e74642683a0415ccdcd6c54352c911c1b81588c7",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
